result.name: 橘焱胡同燒肉夜食 Gyuen Hutong Yakiniku Dining Bar

reviews.text: A gem with tasty food and extremely amazing staff. The place is a little difficult to locate, on level 3 of a dubious-looking building (as of most buildings in Hong Kong). It’s got a MacDonald’s on level 1, and once you climb up the staircase (or take the lift), the proper restaurant will be there. Their Orion draft beer was very fresh and creamy, should definitely get. The staff recommended the beef skirt, which was so extremely juicy and tender. We also tried their squid sausage, which was crispy on the outside and every chew was filled with balanced, comfortable umami. The meat elections come with an option to be marinated in bbq sauce, but we opted for ours to be seasoned with just salt, and it already tasted amazing enough. I recommend this option. The grilled portobello was juicy. Their A3 wagyu was also v fresh, with the right amount of oozing fats such that it was just lightly salted and peppered and still gave a lingering buttery delish. The staff would do the grill for you, and they were knowledgeable about the extent to grill the items. Subtly, we also realised that the staff made a lot of effort in changing the grill such that there was never any charring or re-use of the grill so that the ingredients were always cooked to their best. Definitely worth a visit. Reasonable price for the quality of food and service! Will pay a return visit (:
Great service! They cook for you at your table. Good food. Limited menu but everything tasted  good.

Real BBQ with charcoal, cooked for you at the bar. With professional staff that serve you with a smile and delicious food at affordable portion and price? 
Absolutely will come back.
A gem in HK and makes it stand apart from all the other "Yakiniku" japanese style BBQ. A place that brings the best of Taiwanese flair to Hong Kong.
Yummy !!!
美食，良好服務態度，優雅嘅環境，唯枱數較少，專注服務客人！
